## Project: FastForward Logistics Internal Operations Dashboard

### Overview
FastForward Logistics is a mid-size freight and supply chain company that currently relies on spreadsheets to monitor operational performance. As the business has scaled, this approach has become inefficient, fragmented, and difficult to present in leadership settings.

This project delivers a **front-end dashboard prototype** that centralizes operational data into a clean, modern, and presentation-ready experience.

---

## Goal
Design and build a **single-page internal dashboard** that enables leadership to quickly understand business performance.

The solution should:
- Present key metrics clearly and efficiently
- Support fast insights during leadership reviews
- Demonstrate strong frontend fundamentals and UX thinking
- Be polished enough for presentation use

The experience should prioritize a **dark-mode, executive-friendly design**.

---

## Problem Statement
Current operational data is spread across spreadsheets, making it difficult to:
- Quickly assess business performance
- Identify trends or risks
- Communicate updates clearly in meetings

A centralized dashboard is needed to provide a **single source of truth**.

---

## Users
**Primary User**
- VP of Operations

**Secondary Users**
- Operations managers  
- Regional leads  
- Analysts monitoring performance  

---

## Functional Requirements
The dashboard must include:
- Shipment volume or revenue overview  
- On-time delivery performance  
- Additional operational metric (orders, exceptions, etc.)

---

## Visual & UX Requirements

### Design Style
- Use **Vuetify dark theme by default**
- Clean, minimal, and uncluttered layout
- Strong hierarchy for quick executive scanning
- Consistent and restrained color palette (no rainbow charts)
- Presentation-ready visual polish
- Maintain consistent left/right page gutters between app bar and content at all breakpoints

---

### Layout Structure (Vuetify)

Use `v-app`, `v-app-bar`, `v-container`, `v-row`, and `v-col`.

#### 1. App Bar
- Title: **FastForward Logistics**
- Global **month filter (dropdown or select)**
- Filter defaults to **"All"**

---

#### 2. Summary KPI Cards
Display **4 cards in a row (desktop)**:
- Revenue / Shipment Value  
- Shipment Volume  
- On-Time Delivery Rate  
- Orders / Exceptions  

Each card must include:
- Metric label  
- Large primary value  
- Change vs previous month  
- Up/down arrow indicator  
- Color + icon (not color-only)

---

#### 3. Charts Layout

**Row 1**
- Left: **Bar chart** (monthly metric, e.g., revenue or shipments)  
- Right: **Line chart** (trend over time)

**Row 2**
- Full-width **line or area chart** (performance trend such as delivery rate)

---

## Interaction Behavior

### Global Month Filter
Controls all dashboard data.

**When a specific month is selected:**
- Cards update to that month’s values  
- Charts highlight or focus on that month  

**When "All" is selected:**
- Cards show yearly totals or averages  
- Charts display full 12-month trends  

---

### KPI Trend Indicators
Each summary card should:
- Compare against the **previous month**
- Show:
  - Up arrow for increase  
  - Down arrow for decrease  
- Include visual + textual reinforcement (not color alone)

---

### Charts Behavior
Charts must:
- Use `chart.js` with `vue-chartjs`  
- Include tooltips on hover  
- Smoothly update when filter changes  
- Maintain readable axes and labels  
- Be visually consistent with dark theme  

---

## Responsive Requirements
- Mobile-first layout  
- Cards stack vertically on small screens  
- Charts resize fluidly  
- Maintain readability at all sizes  

---

## Accessibility Requirements
- Sufficient contrast in dark mode  
- Do not rely on color alone  
- Use icons + labels for meaning  
- Ensure readable typography and spacing  
- Ensure filter is keyboard accessible  

---

## Data Requirements

Use a **local JSON dataset only** (no API calls).

Dataset must include:
- 12 months of data (Jan–Dec 2025)

Each month should include:
- Revenue / shipment value (upward trend)  
- Shipment volume (with possible seasonality)  
- On-time delivery rate (%)  
- Orders or exceptions  

Data must support:
- Monthly filtering  
- “All” aggregation (totals or averages)  

---

## Technical Requirements

- Vue 3 + TypeScript  
- Vuetify 3 for UI components  
- Material Design Icons  
- Chart.js + vue-chartjs  
- Local JSON data (no backend)  
- Single-page application  

